HEADWORD: Silene
<hw>Si*le"ne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Silenus</ets>, the attendant of Bacchus.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of caryophyllaceous plants, usually covered with a viscid
secretion by which insects are caught; catchfly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

